Here's how to implement all three pieces:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button (in `EditProductPage.xaml`)

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

In your ViewModel:

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
async Task Back()
{
    if (HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 2. Guard the Hardware/Swipe Back (in `AppShell.xaml.cs`)

The custom back button handles taps, but you also need to guard the system back gesture. Use `OnNavigating` with `GetDeferral()`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **`BackButtonBehavior.Command`** intercepts the Shell back button tap — use `TextOverride` to change its label to "Cancel".
- **`OnNavigating` + `GetDeferral()`** catches system back (swipe/hardware button). You **must** call `GetDeferral()` before any `await`, then `deferral.Complete()` after.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so you only guard backward navigation, not forward or tab switches.
